cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PF

This paper presents a framework for high-performance computing in Scala, which involves parallel operations on distributed data structures. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the implementation of these data structures using the Traversable/Builder pattern, which is related to Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the correctness and safety of communication algorithms, which is related to Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents empirical results comparing the performance of the framework with other MPI-bindings, which is related to Performance (cs.PF) sub-category.
